Subject: [PATCH] net: phy: qca808x: disable EEE on QCA8084 QXGMII links

QCA8084 links running over the 10G-QXGMII package path can report
MAC-facing RX CRC and fragment errors when EEE is negotiated with the
link partner. On a Xiaomi BE7000 WAN link, clearing the copper PHY EEE
advertisement register and restarting autoneg stopped the raw XGMAC RX
CRC/fragment counters from increasing, including under burst ping
traffic.

Disable EEE for QCA8084 PHYs using the 10G-QXGMII interface through
phylib so that EEE modes are not advertised or re-enabled from userspace.

Signed-off-by: Igor Kravchenko <igor.kravchenko05@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/net/phy/qcom/qca808x.c | 10 +++++++++-
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/phy/qcom/qca808x.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/qcom/qca808x.c
@@ -1097,6 +1097,14 @@ static int qca8084_config_init(struct ph
 	else
 		qca808x_fill_possible_interfaces(phydev);
 
+	if (phydev->interface == PHY_INTERFACE_MODE_10G_QXGMII) {
+		/* EEE negotiated on the copper side can disturb the QCA8084
+		 * QXGMII/XGMAC RX path, showing up as raw XGMAC CRC and
+		 * fragment errors. Keep QXGMII package links out of EEE.
+		 */
+		phy_disable_eee(phydev);
+	}
+
 	/* Configure the ADC to convert the signal using falling edge
 	 * instead of the default rising edge.
 	 */
